Question;Answer
In ancient Greece, how were people organized (cities, countries, kingdoms)?;Into city-states
Who reformed Athens to make it later become a democracy?;Solon
What is the type of government where citizens vote for all the laws?;Democracy
How many branches of government did Athens have?;3
Why did Athens have their government divided into different branches?;They did this so a tyrant (dictator) would never take over.
Who was the first people to create the idea of a citizen?;Athenians
Which Greek statesman defended the idea of democracy?;Pericles
When was the Classical Age of Greece?;The fifth and fourth centuries B.C.
What kind of government does the United States of America have?;A republic, or, a representative democracy
